Samba talloc api is usefull, but its implementation is infernal.
1. Sizeof talloc_chunk is 88 bytes (amd64) + align is 16 bytes. So any leaf of the tree will weigh minimum 96 bytes.
2. Unnecessary features cannot be simply switched off.
3. All-in-one. Ex : append_buffer is defected by design.
4. It depends on samba utils, which is very hard to dig out.
5. WAF build system.

This is lightweight implementation of cutted talloc api. License - LGPL v3.
1. Minimal sizeof talloc_chunk is 32 bytes (amd64).
2. Save memory without performance penalties.
2. Configurable extensions.
3. Cake build system. Project is ready to be added as git submodule to existing CMake project.


Implemented & covered by tests
core:
void *  talloc ( const void * ctx, size_t length );
void *  talloc_zero ( const void * ctx, size_t length );
void *  talloc_realloc ( const void * ctx, size_t length );
uint8_t talloc_free ( void * ctx );

helpers:
void *  talloc_new ( const void * ctx );
char *  talloc_strdup ( const void * ctx, const char * str );
char *  talloc_strndup ( const void * ctx, const char * str, size_t length );

extensions:
uint8_t talloc_set_destructor ( const void * ctx, void ( * destructor ) ( void * parent_data ) );

Work is in progress.
